---
By: Meister Eckhart
Locus:
  Page: 441
  Verse: 13
Tags:
  - ''
---
Spirituality is not to be learned by flight from the world, by running away
from things, or by turning solitary and going apart from the world. Rather,
we learn an inner solitude wherever or with whomsoever we may be. We must
learn to penetrate things and find God there.
